HEADWORD: Aweather
<hw>A*weath"er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>a-</ets> + <ets>weather</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>On
the weather side, or toward the wind; in the direction from which the
wind blows; -- opposed to <contr>alee</contr>; <as>as, helm
<ex>aweather</ex>!</as></def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

